                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <cell><p>Cost (<dollar/>)</p></cell>
                                <cell><p><m>\hphantom{0000}</m> </p></cell>
                                <cell><p><m>\hphantom{0000}</m> </p></cell>
                                <cell><p><m>\hphantom{0000}</m> </p></cell>
                                <cell><p><m>\hphantom{0000}</m> </p></cell>
                                <cell><p><m>\hphantom{0000}</m> </p></cell>
                            </row>
                    </tabular></table>
                </p></li>
                <li><p>Choose scales for the axes and graph the equation.</p></li>
                <li><p>How much does the annual cost of driving increase when the mileage increases from <m>8000</m> to <m>12,000</m> miles? Illustrate this amount on the graph.</p></li>
